lab_notes: This sample also has the insect that I first thought was Atanycolus (I don't really think it is)
Sample also has ash samaras for tree ID. There is also a slightly smaller bluish buprestid
One of the males is a bit smaller than the other males
A larger buprestid (not EAB) was found
Many smaller buprestids including (possibly) Agrilus bilineatus
Also a cerambycid that may feed on ash trees (the small kind with long antennae)
Perhaps a sawfly that we also saw in the ash common garden
